---
import RealestateLayout from '../../../layouts/RealestateLayout.astro';
import CtaButton from '../../../components/CtaButton.astro';
import NewsletterSignup from '../../../components/NewsletterSignup.astro';
---

<RealestateLayout
  title="Markham Real Estate | Neighbourhood Profile | Cory Wong, Real Estate Agent"
  description="Markham real estate neighbourhood profile: housing types, price ranges, schools, transit, and market insights from Cory Wong, Real Estate Agent, Trustwell Realty Inc., Brokerage."
  canonicalPath="/neighbourhoods/markham"
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Markham Real Estate: A Neighbourhood Profile</h1>
      <p class="page-hero__subtitle">
        Cory Wong, Real Estate Agent | Trustwell Realty Inc., Brokerage
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <article class="profile">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="profile__content">
        <p class="profile__intro">
          Markham is one of the most sought-after communities in the Greater Toronto Area. It
          offers what many GTA buyers are looking for: space, strong schools, good transit
          connections, and a range of housing types at prices that remain accessible compared
          to Toronto proper.
        </p>

        <h2>Character and Feel</h2>
        <p>
          Markham is a city of distinct communities. Cornell, Unionville, Markham Village,
          Berczy Village, and Cathedraltown each have their own feel and price range.
        </p>
        <p>
          Unionville draws buyers who want heritage character and a walkable main street.
          Cornell and Berczy Village are newer, master-planned communities with modern detached
          and semi-detached homes. Markham Village is established, with mature trees and
          proximity to historic downtown Markham.
        </p>
        <p>
          The city has a large and active East Asian community. There's a strong local food
          scene, well-regarded schools, and a range of community organizations.
        </p>

        <h2>Who Buys in Markham</h2>
        <p>
          The typical buyer in Markham is a move-up buyer or a first-time buyer choosing space
          over proximity to downtown Toronto. Families prioritize Markham for its schools,
          particularly at the secondary level. First-time buyers are drawn by the price
          difference from inner Toronto. Investors buy here for long-term rental demand driven
          by York University, Seneca at York, and steady job growth in the technology corridor
          along Highway 7.
        </p>

        <h2>Housing Types and Price Ranges</h2>
        <ul class="price-list">
          <li><strong>Detached homes:</strong> approximately $1.1M to $2.5M, depending on location and size</li>
          <li><strong>Semi-detached homes:</strong> $900K to $1.3M in most areas</li>
          <li><strong>Freehold townhomes:</strong> $750K to $1.1M</li>
          <li><strong>Condos (near Highway 7):</strong> from approximately $550K</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Unionville and Angus Glen carry premiums. Cornell and Cathedraltown are priced more accessibly.</p>
        <p class="profile__disclaimer">
          These are general estimates based on market activity in early 2026. Actual prices vary
          by property. Speak with Cory for a current assessment.
        </p>

        <h2>Transit and Highways</h2>
        <p>
          Markham is accessible via the 404/DVP corridor and Highway 407. The Stouffville GO
          line serves Unionville, Mount Joy, and Markham stations, with trains to Union Station
          in under an hour during peak hours. York Region Transit connects to TTC subway at
          Finch and Sheppard stations.
        </p>
        <p>
          For buyers who drive, Markham offers straightforward access to Highway 401 and
          downtown Toronto.
        </p>

        <h2>Amenities and Schools</h2>
        <p>
          Pacific Mall, the largest indoor Asian mall in North America, is a community hub.
          First Markham Place, Markville Mall, and smaller retail strips cover daily needs.
        </p>
        <p>
          Top-rated public secondary schools include Unionville High School and Milliken Mills
          High School. The York Catholic District School Board serves Catholic families.
        </p>

        <h2>Real Estate Perspective</h2>
        <p>
          Markham has held its value through the GTA market correction better than many areas.
          Demand from move-up buyers and investors remains steady. Active listings have increased
          in 2025 and 2026, giving buyers more choice than in previous years. Correctly-priced
          homes in good condition are still moving.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you're buying in Markham, work with an agent who knows the individual communities.
          Prices and conditions differ significantly between Unionville and the condo market
          near Highway 7.
        </p>

        <div class="profile__cta">
          <CtaButton href="/contact" label="Book a Consultation" variant="primary" />
        </div>

        <p class="profile__compliance">
          Cory Wong, Real Estate Agent. Real estate services provided through Trustwell Realty
          Inc., Brokerage.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <NewsletterSignup heading="Get GTA Market Updates" />
</RealestateLayout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    padding: var(--space-2xl) 0 var(--space-xl);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .page-hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.5rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .page-hero__subtitle {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .profile {
    padding: 0 0 var(--space-xl);
  }

  .profile__content {
    max-width: 36rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .profile__intro {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-md);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .profile__content h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .profile__content p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .price-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .price-list li {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .price-list li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.5rem;
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    background: var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: 50%;
  }

  .profile__disclaimer {
    font-size: 0.8125rem !important;
    font-style: italic;
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  .profile__cta {
    text-align: center;
    margin: var(--space-xl) 0;
  }

  .profile__compliance {
    font-size: 0.8125rem !important;
    opacity: 0.7;
    font-style: italic;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding-top: var(--space-md);
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
  }
</style>
